#: ../../docs/classes/class_checkbox.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_checkbox.rst:19
msgid ""
"A checkbox allows the user to make a binary choice (choosing only one of "
"two possible options). It's similar to :ref:`CheckButton "
"<class_CheckButton>` in functionality, but it has a different apperance. "
"To follow established UX patterns, it's recommended to use CheckBox when "
"toggling it has **no** immediate effect on something. For instance, it "
"should be used when toggling it will only do something once a "
"confirmation button is pressed."
msgstr ""

